Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Persona swap — INTENTIONALLY EMPTY (see rationale)

This patch slot is reserved but contains no code changes.

Rationale (Spike 2, see bundles/maker-lab/PHASE-0-REPORT.md):

The upstream Open-LLM-VTuber backend already supports per-connection
persona swap via the `switch-config` WebSocket message. Maker-lab ships
three character YAMLs (kid / tween / adult tutor) and drives the swap
server-side on `maker_start_session` — the web client needs no patch
to participate.

We keep this file as a numbered slot so:

  1. The patch-series numbering stays contiguous (0001..0006), which
     matches the `build-pet-linux.sh` apply loop.
  2. If upstream changes direction and persona swap moves from the
     server config into a renderer-side selection, we have a pre-named
     slot to fill without renumbering the rest of the series.

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932

No-op — build script tolerates zero-hunk patches.
